parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires in the vehicle, resulting in damage to the vehicle, injury to occupants, and potentially even fatalities.

The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose control while braking, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the brakes make noise when applied
the ABS system fails to engage when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control while braking, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the brakes make noise when applied
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure leading to Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel system failure can cause a vehicle fire, which can result in serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: with the fire originating from the fuel tank or fuel line area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel line leak can cause a fire hazard, as fuel can spill onto the road or ignite from an ignition source, leading to a vehicle fire.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel line under the vehicle
often near the fuel tank or center of the undercarriage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the fuel system can cause a fire hazard, as well as lead to engine stalling or failure, which can increase the risk of an accident.
symptoms: often causing the engine to stall or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver's Seat Malfunction and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the driver's seat can cause a fire, resulting in burns to occupants and potentially leading to a vehicle fire, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The driver's seat starts to burn
and sudden collapse of the seat back.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden collapse of the adjustable driver's seat back can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries to the driver and occupants.
symptoms: The driver's seat back collapses with no warning
